<p>So what I have is a generic Method with multiple generic types.</p>  <p>Now I'd like to call this Method this way (using the types of a and b and just specifying the return type):</p>  <pre><code>class Example {      T1 GenericMethod&lt;T1, T2, T3&gt;(T2 parameter1, T3 parameter2)      {         T1 returnValue = default(T1);          // ... Do something with returnType, parameter1 and parameter2          return returnValue;     }      void AccessGenericMethod()     {         var a = new Foo1();         var b = new Foo2();         var result = GenericMethod&lt;ReturnType&gt;(a, b); // doesn't work     } } </code></pre>  <p>And i would like to avoid to call <code>GenericMethod</code> this way</p>  <pre><code>var result GenericMethod&lt;ReturnType, Foo1, Foo2&gt;(a, b); </code></pre>